Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.27,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Detective Agency
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.94,0:00:03.27,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you haven't forgotten, Mori-kun,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.45,0:00:08.40,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,about how much trouble you caused me \Nwhen you worked under me in investigations.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.89,0:00:13.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you suddenly drop \Nin and bring up the past?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.91,0:00:16.40,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you figure it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.40,0:00:19.75,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You're the only one I can count on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.21,0:00:21.77,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,There's no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.77,0:00:24.67,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I need you to help me solve a case.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.26,0:00:27.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I-Inspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.96,0:00:31.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Raise your head, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.53,0:00:36.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It must be a pretty big case if \NInspector Megure is this desperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.36,0:00:39.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What case is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.97,0:00:41.11,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,This.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.47,0:00:44.48,Headline,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Japanese Literature Scholar \NReigan Yutaka (70) Murdered!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.67,0:00:49.63,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I thought the suspect in this \Ncase was already arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.63,0:00:51.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't it solved?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.72,0:00:52.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.98,0:00:56.92,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Just before we were going \Nto start prosecuting him,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.24,0:00:59.74,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,it was all overturned!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.97,0:01:00.94,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.08,0:01:07.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When the countdown reaches zero, use your \Ndetective skills to produce an answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.88,0:01:11.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Something's happened at the MPD!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.59,0:01:13.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A mysterious case has been overturned!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.76,0:01:15.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.31,0:01:17.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.12,0:01:19.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.99,0:03:03.99,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(396,1)}The Job Request From Inspector Megure
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.87,0:03:01.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Job Request From Inspector Megure!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.72,0:03:08.50,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,As you know, the incident \Noccurred three weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.04,0:03:12.00,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The famous Japanese literature scholar,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.58,0:03:16.18,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Reigan Yutaka, was found stabbed to \Ndeath in his home in Yotsubadai.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.63,0:03:17.46,Yutaka,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Reigan Yutaka (70) \NJapanese Literature Scholar
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.69,0:03:22.13,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He was killed the previous \Nnight around eight o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.13,0:03:24.59,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It wasn't long before we had a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.38,0:03:25.47,Ryuji,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Maihama Ryuji (33) \NSuspect
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.72,0:03:29.23,Koichi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Yao Koichi (35) \NWitness
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.87,0:03:29.23,DCMain,YAO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I saw him last night around eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.00,0:03:40.64,DCItalic,YAO,0000,0000,0000,,I'd seen him at a bar near the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.64,0:03:43.25,DCItalic,YAO,0000,0000,0000,,He said he was Reigan-sensei's nephew.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.63,0:03:50.00,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He was the victim's nephew and \Nself-proclaimed event producer Maihama Ryuji.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.00,0:03:52.00,Furniture,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Furniture \NHome Improvement Store
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.00,0:03:55.99,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We learned the day before the murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.99,0:04:00.17,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Maihama purchased the knife \Nthat was the murder weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.01,0:04:04.01,HQ,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Reigan Yutaka Murder \NInvestigation HQ
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.97,0:04:04.01,DCItalic,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,On the night of the murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.47,0:04:08.41,DCItalic,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Maihama claims he was in his \Napartment in Sasago-cho,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.41,0:04:09.77,DCItalic,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,but no one can verify his alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.83,0:04:14.77,DCItalic,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,He also claims he purchased \Nbut lost the knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.38,0:04:20.15,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Maihama is Reigan's only living relative.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.39,0:04:25.66,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently he was telling everyone that \NReigan's fortune would eventually become his.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.15,0:04:27.22,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.93,0:04:29.66,DCItalic,REIGAN,0000,0000,0000,,I've remained a bachelor until now,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.91,0:04:33.82,DCItalic,REIGAN,0000,0000,0000,,but I finally found someone I want to marry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.77,0:04:50.01,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Maihama had no alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.01,0:04:51.72,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,His uncle's fortune was his motive,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.03,0:04:55.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and he bought the knife the day before.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.48,0:04:59.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,There's even a witness who saw him at the \Ncrime scene when the murder took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.55,0:05:07.00,DCItalic,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Maihama Ryuji,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.00,0:05:10.24,DCItalic,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,you're under arrest for the \Nmurder of Reigan Yutaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.63,0:05:13.25,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.76,0:05:17.40,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Even after his arrest, Maihama \Ncontinued to deny that he did it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.40,0:05:19.88,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,but naturally, we could still prosecute.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.88,0:05:24.77,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,However, yesterday, with two days \Nremaining on his detention period,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.77,0:05:27.32,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,he gave an unbelievable statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.32,0:05:28.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Which was?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.81,0:05:35.54,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, I'm going to be framed \Nfor murder, so I'll tell you the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.54,0:05:39.10,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,I actually have an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.10,0:05:40.02,DCItalic,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,An alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.78,0:05:45.94,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,The night my uncle was killed, I was \Ncommitting a burglary in Sasago-cho.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.20,0:05:47.70,DCItalic,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Burglary?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.94,0:05:49.20,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.83,0:05:56.33,Burglar,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Sasago-cho Burglar
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.32,0:05:56.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, \NI remember that case.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.60,0:05:59.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A burglar entered a home in Sasago-cho.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.35,0:06:04.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After staying there for over an hour, \Nhe stole about 500 thousand yen in cash.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.57,0:06:10.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The burglar's face wasn't seen, \Nbut Maihama claims it was him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.16,0:06:16.35,DCMain,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,While I was there, I had \Nsomething to drink and eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.17,0:06:19.85,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that the burglar drank and ate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.85,0:06:24.61,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The teeth marks we collected \Nfrom the food matched Maihama's.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.96,0:06:27.56,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We even found the 500 thousand yen he hid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.65,0:06:35.00,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Maihama was definitely the burglar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.00,0:06:39.62,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But if that's true, then he has an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.16,0:06:41.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,An alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.24,0:06:42.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.95,0:06:46.87,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The burglar entered the \Nhome in Sasago-cho at 7PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.55,0:06:52.89,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Since he was there for over \Nan hour, he left after eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.19,0:06:58.89,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Meanwhile, Reigan was murdered in his \Nhome in Yotsubadai around eight as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.23,0:07:04.22,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It takes over an hour by car to travel \Nbetween Sasago-cho and Yotsubadai.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.22,0:07:07.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So it was impossible for \NMaihama to murder Reigan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.02,0:07:10.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But, Inspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.60,0:07:15.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There's a witness who says he saw Maihama at \Nthe crime scene at the time of the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.50,0:07:18.91,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday, that witness said...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.12,0:07:22.36,DCItalic,YAO,0000,0000,0000,,I actually lied about seeing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.36,0:07:23.67,DCItalic,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.04,0:07:29.17,DCItalic,YAO,0000,0000,0000,,He seemed like a bad guy when I saw him \Nat the bar, so I thought I'd frame him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.41,0:07:32.14,DCItalic,YAO,0000,0000,0000,,But I felt guilty about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.14,0:07:34.18,DCItalic,YAO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for making it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.39,0:07:36.11,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,He made it up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.11,0:07:38.18,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, regarding the knife...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.64,0:07:41.69,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,I bought it to use during the burglary.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.02,0:07:45.16,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,I buried it behind my apartment \Nbuilding after I used it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.00,0:07:47.94,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.08,0:07:52.45,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same as the one \Nfound in Reigan's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.68,0:07:55.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He must've planned all of it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.71,0:08:00.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so he wouldn't lose his inheritance and \Nto avoid being convicted of murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.67,0:08:02.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's too convenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.26,0:08:07.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's obvious he'd be a suspect \Nif Reigan were murdered
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.36,0:08:12.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so he allowed himself to be \Narrested so he could overturn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.44,0:08:17.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The witness who went back on his testimony \Nis working with him, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.56,0:08:23.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He probably just bought \Nanother one of these knives.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.44,0:08:29.15,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I know he committed the \Nburglary to create an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.15,0:08:33.99,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The problem is how in two locations, \Nseparated by an hour's travel,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.51,0:08:38.23,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,a single human committed \Na burglary in Sasago-cho
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.23,0:08:40.99,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,while murdering Reigan in Yotsubadai.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.23,0:08:46.01,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Unless we can solve that, even if we \Ncan prosecute him for the burglary,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.01,0:08:49.71,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,which was material evidence, we can't \Nprosecute him for Reigan's murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.28,0:08:57.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So we spent all day yesterday \Ntrying to solve the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.04,0:09:00.52,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,However, we ran into a dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.67,0:09:05.02,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm asking for your help!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.47,0:09:10.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, I, Mori Kogoro, shall assist you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.74,0:09:14.23,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I have no faith in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.23,0:09:19.14,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But when you're asleep, your detective \Nskills become mind-boggling.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.14,0:09:21.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, I'm not sure how to respond to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.14,0:09:27.21,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A burglary and a murder in two \Ndifferent places at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.19,0:09:36.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I've got it, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.33,0:09:41.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Immediately after committing \Nthe burglary in Sasago-cho,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.71,0:09:44.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,he killed Reigan who he'd \Nasked to meet him nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.91,0:09:51.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then he put the body in a car and drove \Nit to Reigan's home in Yotsubadai.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.19,0:09:53.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Mori-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.41,0:09:59.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't the forensics team have \Nnoticed if the body had been moved?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.85,0:10:04.44,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Reigan was murdered inside his own home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.44,0:10:07.37,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,There's no sign the murder was staged.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.47,0:10:12.02,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,If anything was staged, it was the burglary.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.24,0:10:15.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. Go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.01,0:10:19.04,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,About the burglary.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.04,0:10:23.39,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's strange that he stayed \Nthere for an entire hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.81,0:10:29.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We're certain that the burglar entered \Nthe home in Sasago-cho at 7 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.55,0:10:31.90,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Tenyama Hide-san, who lives alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.90,0:10:36.11,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,had just begun to watch the seven \No'clock news while eating dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.14,0:10:37.94,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.31,0:10:40.09,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Move, and I'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.70,0:10:46.17,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}And I don't want you seeing my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.82,0:10:45.58,Hide,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Tenyama Hide (73) \NVictim
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.45,0:10:48.86,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the money?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.16,0:10:52.41,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't underestimate me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.07,0:10:56.39,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Though she tried to tell him \Nwhere she kept her money,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.39,0:10:59.22,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Hide-san was suddenly struck \Nand lost consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.67,0:11:03.10,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,She awoke an hour later at eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.10,0:11:07.64,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,She heard the sounds of a TV \Nshow that starts at eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.89,0:11:11.69,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,You're finally awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.69,0:11:14.73,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,I looked for your money, but I couldn't \Nfind it, so I've been waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.16,0:11:16.73,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the money?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.73,0:11:19.74,DCItalic,HIDE,0000,0000,0000,,In the middle drawer of the dresser.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.94,0:11:21.03,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.03,0:11:24.29,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,I can't have you calling \Nthe police right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.06,0:11:32.54,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The second time Hide-san \Nawoke was the next morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.26,0:11:40.50,DCItalic,HIDE,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.25,0:11:43.06,DCItalic,HIDE,0000,0000,0000,,The money!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.06,0:11:45.18,DCItalic,HIDE,0000,0000,0000,,The money in the dresser!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.18,0:11:51.52,DCItalic,HIDE,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, police?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.84,0:11:55.23,DCItalic,HIDE,0000,0000,0000,,I've been burglarized!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.28,0:12:02.93,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.43,0:12:05.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.77,0:12:07.31,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I've figured it out, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.31,0:12:07.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.34,0:12:09.63,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.63,0:12:12.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Maihama stepped out for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.71,0:12:14.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There are two points to focus on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.71,0:12:17.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,First, that Maihama blindfolded Hide-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.40,0:12:20.55,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and second, that he knocked her out twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.55,0:12:21.85,DCMain,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't underestimate me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.02,0:12:26.83,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After entering at seven and \Nknocking Hide-san unconscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.83,0:12:28.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Maihama recorded the TV program.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.68,0:12:34.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He quickly drove to Yotsubadai \Nand murdered Reigan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.35,0:12:36.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It happened after eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.28,0:12:43.86,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then he returned to Sasago-cho, \Nreplayed the video he recorded,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.32,0:12:46.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and woke Hide-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.68,0:12:50.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was probably after nine by then,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.87,0:12:55.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but because of the audio of \Nthe TV show Maihama recorded,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.12,0:12:55.12,TopTen,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,It's 8 o'clock! Music Top Ten
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.41,0:12:57.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,he made her believe it was eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.73,0:13:00.63,DCItalic,HIDE,0000,0000,0000,,In the middle drawer of the dresser.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.03,0:13:04.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then he knocked out Hide-san again,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.60,0:13:08.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and made it appear as though \Nhe'd been there for an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.34,0:13:14.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Maihama wasn't in Hide-san's \Nhome the whole time after he entered.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.13,0:13:17.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He left and traveled back \Nand forth to Yotsubadai
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.78,0:13:20.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,while Hide-san was knocked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.12,0:13:24.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow. That's perfect, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.05,0:13:27.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This is the first time the \NInspector's asked for my help.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.77,0:13:30.21,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,How could I disappoint him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.21,0:13:31.41,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.60,0:13:36.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No, it was an honor to serve you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.33,0:13:40.61,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, we considered that possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.61,0:13:41.92,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,However, it's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.21,0:13:43.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.34,0:13:49.02,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot to mention that \Nwhen Tenyama Hide-san awoke,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.02,0:13:54.15,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,she heard not only the sounds of the \NTV show, but also a fire truck siren.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.84,0:14:00.31,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Maihama demanded the location of the \Nmoney while she could hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.66,0:14:02.42,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We confirmed with the fire \Ndepartment that eight
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.42,0:14:07.32,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,was the only time a fire truck was \Ndispatched in Sasago-cho that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.54,0:14:09.85,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.85,0:14:13.35,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Maihama never left.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.38,0:14:15.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.60,0:14:22.00,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If he didn't want his face to be seen, \Nhe only needed to wear a mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.65,0:14:27.23,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There must be some reason he \Nblocked Hide-san's vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.81,0:14:30.29,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.98,0:14:40.07,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,At 8PM on the night in question,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.07,0:14:44.15,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maihama Ryuji was threatening \NTenyama Hide-san in Sasago-cho.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.39,0:14:48.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So how did he kill Reigan in Yotsubadai?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.63,0:14:53.25,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Is it not coming yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.25,0:14:53.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.95,0:14:55.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Who's coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.44,0:15:00.79,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Not who, but those weird \Nexclamations you always make.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.01,0:15:03.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that convenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.02,0:15:06.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But, Inspector,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.00,0:15:11.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,are we sure Hide-san heard \Nthe fire truck siren?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.98,0:15:12.88,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.88,0:15:15.35,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We checked with her, so I'm certain of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.88,0:15:18.10,DCItalic,HIDE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I know I heard it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.31,0:15:22.35,DCItalic,HIDE,0000,0000,0000,,And I smelled something burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.79,0:15:24.86,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Smelled something burning?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.34,0:15:29.26,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't make sense that \Nshe smelled anything though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.26,0:15:32.61,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently it was a prank call.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.98,0:15:37.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, there was no fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.13,0:15:38.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.48,0:15:41.79,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But a fire truck was stilled dispatched.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.08,0:15:45.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe hearing the siren made her \Nthink she smelled something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.62,0:15:48.66,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.66,0:15:52.33,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,She seemed to have it together, \Nbut she's an old woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.33,0:15:54.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,She was confused about all sorts of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.83,0:15:57.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did she mention something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.61,0:15:58.49,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.49,0:16:01.43,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,She claimed she didn't hear \Na sound she expected to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.65,0:16:04.36,DCItalic,HIDE,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the TV and the siren,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.36,0:16:07.94,DCItalic,HIDE,0000,0000,0000,,but I didn't hear the bathtub notification.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.18,0:16:11.20,DCItalic,HIDE,0000,0000,0000,,I set it to be ready at 8 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.20,0:16:12.69,DCItalic,HIDE,0000,0000,0000,,Strange, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.69,0:16:13.95,DCItalic,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.16,0:16:16.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she just missed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.33,0:16:18.05,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.05,0:16:21.17,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, is it still not coming, Mori-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.17,0:16:21.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.96,0:16:24.21,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Get sleepy already.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.42,0:16:27.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But I got plenty of sleep last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.60,0:16:31.38,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You're unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.38,0:16:35.09,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It reminds me of all the cases that \Nwere nearly unsolved because of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.76,0:16:41.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not responsible for this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.81,0:16:46.10,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Today's the last day we have left, Mori-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.26,0:16:49.98,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, we're going\Nto have to drop the charges,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.98,0:16:52.49,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,even though we know he's the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.38,0:16:57.53,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, this is Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.07,0:17:00.00,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.00,0:17:02.50,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-kun's doing his best right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.92,0:17:04.87,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Have some faith in your senior.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.05,0:17:08.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. If only I hadn't \Nslept so deeply last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.25,0:17:12.63,DCMain,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,We're just wasting time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.89,0:17:16.84,DCMain,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Take me to the burglary investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.84,0:17:21.01,DCMain,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Personally, I wish I could \Nadmit to killing my uncle,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.01,0:17:25.06,DCMain,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,but I have an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.58,0:17:31.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If I drink...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.08,0:17:36.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,...and stuff myself, I should \Nstart to feel sleepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.80,0:17:41.86,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This old man's confused.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.86,0:17:44.20,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Confused?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.20,0:17:46.47,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Was Hide-san really confused, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.93,0:17:52.16,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If Hide-san's perception \Nwasn't wrong, what then?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.58,0:17:55.67,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's it. So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.58,0:17:57.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.88,0:18:02.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What if everything Hide-san said is right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.08,0:18:09.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And if you consider the culprit blindfolded \NHide-san and knocked her out twice,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.25,0:18:11.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,does anything become clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.57,0:18:13.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.82,0:18:15.07,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.15,0:18:17.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The bathroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.35,0:18:21.80,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I was stupid to think I could count on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.39,0:18:24.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.30,0:18:27.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't stay here forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.04,0:18:29.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Just hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.96,0:18:34.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Uh huh. Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.43,0:18:35.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.83,0:18:38.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He seems to have had an epiphany.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.32,0:18:39.75,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.75,0:18:42.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, he wants you to check
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.45,0:18:46.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,if any fire trucks were \Ndispatched to Yotsubadai that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.34,0:18:48.01,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.52,0:18:56.68,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Yes. I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.68,0:18:57.85,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.41,0:19:02.32,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,A truck responded to a small fire at 8 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.82,0:19:03.83,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.11,0:19:06.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.27,0:19:12.00,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Is this it, Mori-kun?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.37,0:19:14.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I feel refreshed \Nafter using the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.33,0:19:16.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The mystery is clear to me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.13,0:19:18.01,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad I didn't leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.91,0:19:23.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Cutting to the chase, \NInspector, Maihama did leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.60,0:19:26.54,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What? I told you, that's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.54,0:19:28.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Not alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.96,0:19:31.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He took Tenyama Hide-san with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.48,0:19:32.29,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.72,0:19:33.98,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.60,0:19:38.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After entering Hide-san's \Nhome at seven o'clock,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.80,0:19:39.90,DCItalic,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't underestimate me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.90,0:19:44.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,he knocked her out and \Nheaded to Yotsubadai
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.84,0:19:48.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,with the unconscious Hide-san in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.28,0:19:53.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then he murdered Reigan and \Nstarted a small fire nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.38,0:19:56.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then he called the fire department.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.59,0:20:01.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He also called in a false report \Nto the Sasago-cho fire department.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.01,0:20:07.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,As he heard the fire truck approaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.33,0:20:11.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Maihama turned on the TV in \Nhis car and woke Hide-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.13,0:20:15.73,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,You're finally awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.68,0:20:21.74,DCItalic,MAIHAMA,0000,0000,0000,,I looked for your money, but I couldn't \Nfind it, so I've been waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.94,0:20:25.99,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After getting the money's location \Nout of her, he knocked her out again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.76,0:20:29.99,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He took Hide-san back to \Nher home in Sasago-cho,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.46,0:20:32.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,placed her in her original position,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.37,0:20:35.31,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and made it seem as though \Nhe was there the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.58,0:20:42.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Maihama blindfolded Hide-san \Nnot to confuse her about the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.47,0:20:47.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but to make her believe she heard the \NTV and siren in her home in Sasago-cho,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.17,0:20:52.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so she wouldn't realize she was actually \Nin a car parked in Yotsubadai.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.48,0:20:53.96,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.96,0:20:58.73,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Tenyama Hide-san believes she was in \Nher own home the whole time, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.14,0:21:03.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She was taken back and forth to \NYotsubadai while she was unconscious
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.57,0:21:07.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so she would confirm Maihama's alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.58,0:21:12.75,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,However, Maihama ended up \Nleaving evidence of his scheme.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.17,0:21:15.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hide-san's nose and ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.38,0:21:18.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She smelled the small fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.71,0:21:23.92,Bath,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Bath is ready
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.09,0:21:23.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and she didn't hear her \Nbathtub's notification.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.28,0:21:27.93,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If you examine Maihama's car \Nagain, I'm sure you'll find
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.56,0:21:31.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,evidence that Hide-san was inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.70,0:21:39.79,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's me. We've destroyed Maihama's alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.79,0:21:42.19,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Thoroughly investigate his car.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.42,0:21:43.72,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.72,0:21:48.05,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Your senior didn't let us down.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.70,0:23:14.20,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Detective Agency
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.84,0:23:14.20,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-kun, thanks for the help.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.40,0:23:15.84,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I should get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.84,0:23:18.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I solved the mystery, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.05,0:23:22.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Maihama has a twin with \Nidentical teeth prints.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.25,0:23:26.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,While he was committing the burglary...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.69,0:23:24.96,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.56,0:23:27.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.18,0:23:29.96,DCItalic,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I don't know what I was expecting.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.96,0:23:32.97,DCItalic,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,This is the only time \NI'm asking him for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.04,0:23:37.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, what about Maihama's alibi?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.97,0:23:39.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Maihama is...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.93,0:23:42.72,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This was supposed to have a good ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.98,0:24:09.01,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.29,0:23:46.06,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.06,0:23:49.05,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun is a witness in a murder case?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.33,0:23:53.99,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We're also considering the possibility \Nof theft as we investigate,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.50,0:23:59.05,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,but to be on the safe side, \Nwe're checking everyone's alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.70,0:24:00.69,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.70,0:24:01.04,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,It's the lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.98,0:24:06.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's where we got the drawing done.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.67,0:24:07.71,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hooray!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.71,0:24:09.01,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.01,0:24:15.01,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,"The Detective Boys Become Models"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.72,0:24:13.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is \N"The Detective Boys Become Models!"
